\begin_layout Standard
In this paper 
\begin_inset CommandInset citation
LatexCommand citet
key "strulikHealthHump2015"
literal "false"

\end_inset

 provides a simple explanation for the hump-shaped age-consumption profile.
 Explanations for the hump-shaped age-consumption profile is important,
 because there isn't consensus, yet, about the mechanisms behind it.
 Standard theory predicts consumptions smoothing, which means that no hump
 should be seen.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
This paper creates a utility extension, by letting utility depend on health:
 
\begin_inset Formula 
\[
u\left(c,D\right)=D^{-\alpha}\cdot\tilde{u}\left(c\right)
\]

\end_inset

where 
\begin_inset Formula $\alpha$
\end_inset

 is a parameter, and 
\begin_inset Formula $\tilde{u}\left(c\right)$
\end_inset

 is the utility of consumption.
 He further assumes that 
\begin_inset Formula $h\left(t\right)=0\forall t$
\end_inset

, so deficit accumulation is exogenous in the model.
 There exists a closed form solution of the time of consumption peak, and
 peak consumption level
\begin_inset Foot
status open

